Ranger Help for: trailblaze
============================

SYNTAX:      trailblaze to <player>
             trailblaze to camp <ranger>
             backtrack
USAGE:       Wilderness
SLOT COST:   10
BASE SP:     65
SKILL TYPE:  Cartography

SUMMARY:
Trailblaze allows a Ranger to travel quickly through the wilderness.

TRAILBLAZE TO <PLAYER>:
  Teleport to another player in the same domain. Uses your deep
  knowledge of the terrain to find a shortcut. The target must be a
  visible mortal, and neither of you can be fighting, warded against
  travel, or inside an Eternal Dungeon run.

TRAILBLAZE TO CAMP <RANGER>:
  Visit another Ranger's camp, regardless of domain. Use 'camps'
  to see all registered camps. This is how Rangers visit each
  other's wilderness bases. You cannot trailblaze from or into places
  warded against travel.

BACKTRACK:
  Return to where you trailblazed from. Your origin is remembered
  until you backtrack or trailblaze again. You cannot backtrack while
  fighting, from a warded location, or into a warded location.

